This paper deals with heuristic explorations and algorithmic approaches to solve Su-Doku puzzles, which are combinatorial in nature. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the alldifferent constraint, which is a well-known concept in Constraint Satisfaction Problems (cs.CC), and explores the number of distinct Su-Doku grids (cs.DM). Finally, the paper compares different approaches based on their efficiency, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
